39 /* memory alignment unit - to align stored XASL tree nodes */
40 #define ALIGN_UNIT sizeof(double)
41 #define ALIGN_MASK (ALIGN_UNIT - 1)
42 #define MAKE_ALIGN(x) (((x) & ~ALIGN_MASK) + \
43  (((x) & ALIGN_MASK) ? ALIGN_UNIT : 0))
44 
45 /* to limit size of XASL trees */
46 #define OFFSETS_PER_BLOCK 256
47 #define START_PTR_PER_BLOCK 15
48 #define MAX_PTR_BLOCKS 256
49 
50 #define PTR_BLOCK(ptr) (((UINTPTR) ptr) / sizeof(UINTPTR)) % MAX_PTR_BLOCKS
51 
52 /*
53  * the linear byte stream for store the given XASL tree is allocated
54  * and expanded dynamically on demand by the following amount of bytes
55  */
56 #define STREAM_EXPANSION_UNIT (OFFSETS_PER_BLOCK * sizeof(int))
57 #define BUFFER_EXPANSION 4
58 
59 #define BOUND_VAL (1 << ((OR_INT_SIZE * 8) - 2))
60 
61 /* structure of a visited pointer constant */
62 typedef struct visited_ptr VISITED_PTR;
63 struct visited_ptr
64 {
65  const void *ptr; /* a pointer constant */
66  void *str; /* where the struct pointed by 'ptr' is stored */
67 };
68 
69 /* structure for additional memory during filtered predicate unpacking */
70 typedef struct unpack_extra_buf UNPACK_EXTRA_BUF;
71 struct unpack_extra_buf
72 {
73  char *buff;
74  UNPACK_EXTRA_BUF *next;
75 };
76 
77 /* structure to hold information needed during packing */
78 typedef struct xasl_unpack_info XASL_UNPACK_INFO;
79 struct xasl_unpack_info
80 {
81  char *packed_xasl; /* ptr to packed xasl tree */
82 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
83  THREAD_ENTRY *thrd; /* used for private allocation */
84 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
85 
86  /* blocks of visited pointer constants */
87  VISITED_PTR *ptr_blocks[MAX_PTR_BLOCKS];
88 
89  char *alloc_buf; /* alloced buf */
90 
91  int packed_size; /* packed xasl tree size */
92 
93  /* low-water-mark of visited pointers */
94  int ptr_lwm[MAX_PTR_BLOCKS];
95 
96  /* max number of visited pointers */
97  int ptr_max[MAX_PTR_BLOCKS];
98 
99  int alloc_size; /* alloced buf size */
100 
101  /* list of additional buffers allocated during xasl unpacking */
102  UNPACK_EXTRA_BUF *additional_buffers;
103  /* 1 if additional buffers should be tracked */
104  int track_allocated_bufers;
105 
106  bool use_xasl_clone; /* true, if uses xasl clone */
107 };

235 /*
236  * stx_map_stream_to_xasl_node_header () - Obtain xasl node header from xasl
237  * stream.
238  *
239  * return : error code.
240  * thread_p (in) : thread entry.
241  * xasl_header_p (out) : pointer to xasl node header.
242  * xasl_stream (in) : xasl stream.
243  */
244 int
245 stx_map_stream_to_xasl_node_header (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, XASL_NODE_HEADER * xasl_header_p, char *xasl_stream)
246 {
247  int xasl_stream_header_size = 0, offset = 0;
248  char *ptr = NULL;
249 
250  if (xasl_stream == NULL || xasl_header_p == NULL)
251  {
252  assert (0);
253  return ER_FAILED;
254  }
255  (void) or_unpack_int (xasl_stream, &xasl_stream_header_size);
256  offset = OR_INT_SIZE + /* xasl stream header size */
257  xasl_stream_header_size + /* xasl stream header data */
258  OR_INT_SIZE; /* xasl stream body size */
259  offset = MAKE_ALIGN (offset);
260  ptr = xasl_stream + offset;
261  OR_UNPACK_XASL_NODE_HEADER (ptr, xasl_header_p);
262  return NO_ERROR;
263 }
264 
265 /*
266  * stx_map_stream_to_xasl () -
267  * return: if successful, return 0, otherwise non-zero error code
268  * xasl_tree(in) : pointer to where to return the
269  * root of the unpacked XASL tree
270  * use_xasl_clone(in) : true, if XASL clone is used
271  * xasl_stream(in) : pointer to xasl stream
272  * xasl_stream_size(in) : # of bytes in xasl_stream
273  * xasl_unpack_info_ptr(in) : pointer to where to return the pack info
274  *
275  * Note: map the linear byte stream in disk representation to an XASL tree.
276  *
277  * Note: the caller is responsible for freeing the memory of
278  * xasl_unpack_info_ptr. The free function is stx_free_xasl_unpack_info().
279  */
280 int
281 stx_map_stream_to_xasl (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, XASL_NODE ** xasl_tree, bool use_xasl_clone, char *xasl_stream,
282  int xasl_stream_size, void **xasl_unpack_info_ptr)
283 {
284  XASL_NODE *xasl;
285  char *p;
286  int header_size;
287  int offset;
288  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *unpack_info_p = NULL;
289 
290  if (!xasl_tree || !xasl_stream || !xasl_unpack_info_ptr || xasl_stream_size <= 0)
291  {
292  return ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE;
293  }
294 
295  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, NO_ERROR);
296  stx_init_xasl_unpack_info (thread_p, xasl_stream, xasl_stream_size);
297  unpack_info_p = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
298  unpack_info_p->use_xasl_clone = use_xasl_clone;
299  unpack_info_p->track_allocated_bufers = 1;
300 
301  /* calculate offset to XASL tree in the stream buffer */
302  p = or_unpack_int (xasl_stream, &header_size);
303  offset = sizeof (int) /* [size of header data] */
304  + header_size /* [header data] */
305  + sizeof (int); /* [size of body data] */
306  offset = MAKE_ALIGN (offset);
307 
308  /* restore XASL tree from body data of the stream buffer */
309  xasl = stx_restore_xasl_node (thread_p, xasl_stream + offset);
310  if (xasl == NULL)
311  {
312  stx_free_additional_buff (thread_p, unpack_info_p);
313  stx_free_xasl_unpack_info (unpack_info_p);
314  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, unpack_info_p);
315 
316  goto end;
317  }
318 
319  /* set result */
320  *xasl_tree = xasl;
321  *xasl_unpack_info_ptr = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
322 
323  /* restore header data of new XASL format */
324  p = or_unpack_int (p, &xasl->dbval_cnt);
325  OID_SET_NULL (&xasl->creator_oid);
326  xasl->n_oid_list = 0;
327  xasl->class_oid_list = NULL;
328  xasl->class_locks = NULL;
329  xasl->tcard_list = NULL;
330 
331  /* initialize the query in progress flag to FALSE. Note that this flag is not packed/unpacked. It is strictly a
332  * server side flag. */
333  xasl->query_in_progress = false;
334 end:
335  stx_free_visited_ptrs (thread_p);
336 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
337  stx_set_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p, NULL);
338 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
339 
340  return stx_get_xasl_errcode (thread_p);
341 }
342 
343 /*
344  * stx_map_stream_to_filter_pred () -
345  * return: if successful, return 0, otherwise non-zero error code
346  * pred(in): pointer to where to return the root of the unpacked
347  * filter predicate tree
348  * pred_stream(in): pointer to predicate stream
349  * pred_stream_size(in): # of bytes in predicate stream
350  * pred_unpack_info_ptr(in): pointer to where to return the pack info
351  *
352  * Note: map the linear byte stream in disk representation to an predicate
353  * with context. The caller is responsible for freeing the memory of
354  * (*pred)->unpack_info by calling stx_free_xasl_unpack_info().
355  */
356 int
357 stx_map_stream_to_filter_pred (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PRED_EXPR_WITH_CONTEXT ** pred, char *pred_stream,
358  int pred_stream_size)
359 {
360  PRED_EXPR_WITH_CONTEXT *pwc = NULL;
361  char *p = NULL;
362  int header_size;
363  int offset;
364  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *unpack_info_p = NULL;
365 
366  if (!pred || !pred_stream || pred_stream_size <= 0)
367  {
368  return ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE;
369  }
370 
371  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, NO_ERROR);
372  stx_init_xasl_unpack_info (thread_p, pred_stream, pred_stream_size);
373  unpack_info_p = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
374  unpack_info_p->use_xasl_clone = true;
375  unpack_info_p->track_allocated_bufers = 1;
376 
377  /* calculate offset to filter predicate in the stream buffer */
378  p = or_unpack_int (pred_stream, &header_size);
379  offset = sizeof (int) /* [size of header data] */
380  + header_size /* [header data] */
381  + sizeof (int); /* [size of body data] */
382  offset = MAKE_ALIGN (offset);
383 
384  /* restore XASL tree from body data of the stream buffer */
385  pwc = stx_restore_filter_pred_node (thread_p, pred_stream + offset);
386  if (pwc == NULL)
387  {
388  stx_free_additional_buff (thread_p, unpack_info_p);
389  stx_free_xasl_unpack_info (unpack_info_p);
390  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, unpack_info_p);
391 
392  goto end;
393  }
394 
395  /* set result */
396  pwc->unpack_info = unpack_info_p;
397  *pred = pwc;
398 
399 end:
400  stx_free_visited_ptrs (thread_p);
401 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
402  stx_set_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p, NULL);
403 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
404 
405  return stx_get_xasl_errcode (thread_p);
406 }
407 
408 /*
409  * stx_map_stream_to_func_pred () -
410  * return: if successful, return 0, otherwise non-zero error code
411  * xasl(in) : pointer to where to return the unpacked FUNC_PRED
412  * xasl_stream(in) : pointer to xasl stream
413  * xasl_stream_size(in) : # of bytes in xasl_stream
414  * xasl_unpack_info_ptr(in) : pointer to where to return the pack info
415  */
416 int
417 stx_map_stream_to_func_pred (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FUNC_PRED ** xasl, char *xasl_stream, int xasl_stream_size,
418  void **xasl_unpack_info_ptr)
419 {
420  FUNC_PRED *p_xasl = NULL;
421  char *p = NULL;
422  int header_size;
423  int offset;
424  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *unpack_info_p = NULL;
425 
426  if (!xasl || !xasl_stream || !xasl_unpack_info_ptr || xasl_stream_size <= 0)
427  {
428  return ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE;
429  }
430 
431  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, NO_ERROR);
432  stx_init_xasl_unpack_info (thread_p, xasl_stream, xasl_stream_size);
433  unpack_info_p = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
434  unpack_info_p->use_xasl_clone = false;
435  unpack_info_p->track_allocated_bufers = 1;
436 
437  /* calculate offset to expr XASL in the stream buffer */
438  p = or_unpack_int (xasl_stream, &header_size);
439  offset = sizeof (int) /* [size of header data] */
440  + header_size /* [header data] */
441  + sizeof (int); /* [size of body data] */
442  offset = MAKE_ALIGN (offset);
443 
444  /* restore XASL tree from body data of the stream buffer */
445  p_xasl = stx_restore_func_pred (thread_p, xasl_stream + offset);
446  if (p_xasl == NULL)
447  {
448  stx_free_additional_buff (thread_p, unpack_info_p);
449  stx_free_xasl_unpack_info (unpack_info_p);
450  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, unpack_info_p);
451 
452  goto end;
453  }
454 
455  /* set result */
456  *xasl = p_xasl;
457  *xasl_unpack_info_ptr = unpack_info_p;
458 
459 end:
460  stx_free_visited_ptrs (thread_p);
461 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
462  stx_set_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p, NULL);
463 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
464 
465  return stx_get_xasl_errcode (thread_p);
466 }
467 
468 /*
469  * stx_free_xasl_unpack_info () -
470  * return:
471  * xasl_unpack_info(in): unpack info returned by stx_map_stream_to_xasl ()
472  *
473  * Note: free the memory used for unpacking the xasl tree.
474  */
475 void
476 stx_free_xasl_unpack_info (void *xasl_unpack_info)
477 {
478 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
479  if (xasl_unpack_info)
480  {
481  ((XASL_UNPACK_INFO *) xasl_unpack_info)->thrd = NULL;
482  }
483 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
484 }
485 
486 /*
487  * stx_free_additional_buff () - free additional buffers allocated during
488  * XASL unpacking
489  * return : void
490  * xasl_unpack_info (in) : XASL unpack info
491  */
492 void
493 stx_free_additional_buff (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, void *xasl_unpack_info)
494 {
495  if (xasl_unpack_info)
496  {
497  UNPACK_EXTRA_BUF *add_buff = ((XASL_UNPACK_INFO *) xasl_unpack_info)->additional_buffers;
498  UNPACK_EXTRA_BUF *temp = NULL;
499  while (add_buff != NULL)
500  {
501  temp = add_buff->next;
502  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, add_buff->buff);
503  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, add_buff);
504  add_buff = temp;
505  }
506  }
507 }
508 
509 /*
510  * stx_restore_func_postfix () -
511  * return: if successful, return the offset of position
512  * in disk object where the node is stored, otherwise
513  * return ER_FAILED and error code is set to xasl_errcode.
514  * ptr(in): pointer to an XASL tree node whose type is return type
515  *
516  * Note: store the XASL tree node pointed by 'ptr' into disk
517  * object with the help of stx_build_func_postfix to process
518  * the members of the node.
519  */
520 
521 static AGGREGATE_TYPE *
522 stx_restore_aggregate_type (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr)
523 {
524  AGGREGATE_TYPE *aggregate;
525 
526  if (ptr == NULL)
527  {
528  return NULL;
529  }
530 
531  aggregate = (AGGREGATE_TYPE *) stx_get_struct_visited_ptr (thread_p, ptr);
532  if (aggregate != NULL)
533  {
534  return aggregate;
535  }
536 
537  aggregate = (AGGREGATE_TYPE *) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (*aggregate));
538  if (aggregate == NULL)
539  {
540  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
541  return NULL;
542  }
543 
544  if (stx_mark_struct_visited (thread_p, ptr, aggregate) == ER_FAILED
545  || stx_build_aggregate_type (thread_p, ptr, aggregate) == NULL)
546  {
547  return NULL;
548  }
549 
550  return aggregate;
551 }

1395 static char *
1396 stx_restore_string (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr)
1397 {
1398  char *string;
1399  int length;
1400 
1401  if (ptr == NULL)
1402  {
1403  return NULL;
1404  }
1405 
1406  string = (char *) stx_get_struct_visited_ptr (thread_p, ptr);
1407  if (string != NULL)
1408  {
1409  return string;
1410  }
1411 
1412  length = OR_GET_INT (ptr);
1413 
1414  if (length == -1)
1415  {
1416  /* unpack null-string */
1417  assert (string == NULL);
1418  }
1419  else
1420  {
1421  assert_release (length > 0);
1422 
1423  string = (char *) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, length);
1424  if (string == NULL)
1425  {
1426  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
1427  return NULL;
1428  }
1429 
1430  if (stx_mark_struct_visited (thread_p, ptr, string) == ER_FAILED
1431  || stx_build_string (thread_p, ptr, string) == NULL)
1432  {
1433  return NULL;
1434  }
1435  }
1436 
1437  return string;
1438 }

1440 static DB_VALUE **
1441 stx_restore_db_value_array_extra (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, int nelements, int total_nelements)
1442 {
1443  DB_VALUE **value_array;
1444  int *ints;
1445  int i;
1446  int offset;
1447  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
1448 
1449  value_array = (DB_VALUE **) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (DB_VALUE *) * total_nelements);
1450  if (value_array == NULL)
1451  {
1452  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
1453  return NULL;
1454  }
1455  ints = stx_restore_int_array (thread_p, ptr, nelements);
1456  if (ints == NULL)
1457  {
1458  return NULL;
1459  }
1460 
1461  for (i = 0; i < nelements; i++)
1462  {
1463  offset = ints[i];
1464  value_array[i] = stx_restore_db_value (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
1465  if (value_array[i] == NULL)
1466  {
1467  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
1468  return NULL;
1469  }
1470  assert (value_array[i]->need_clear == false);
1471  }
1472 
1473  for (; i < total_nelements; ++i)
1474  {
1475  value_array[i] = NULL;
1476  }
1477  return value_array;
1478 }

1580 /*
1581  * Restore the regu_variable_list as an array to avoid recursion in the server.
1582  * The array size is restored first, then the array.
1583  */
1584 static REGU_VARIABLE_LIST
1585 stx_restore_regu_variable_list (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr)
1586 {
1587  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regu_var_list;
1588  int offset;
1589  int total;
1590  int i;
1591  char *ptr2;
1592  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
1593 
1594  regu_var_list = (REGU_VARIABLE_LIST) stx_get_struct_visited_ptr (thread_p, ptr);
1595  if (regu_var_list != NULL)
1596  {
1597  return regu_var_list;
1598  }
1599 
1600  ptr2 = or_unpack_int (ptr, &total);
1601  regu_var_list = (REGU_VARIABLE_LIST) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (struct regu_variable_list_node) * total);
1602  if (regu_var_list == NULL)
1603  {
1604  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
1605  return NULL;
1606  }
1607  if (stx_mark_struct_visited (thread_p, ptr, regu_var_list) == ER_FAILED)
1608  {
1609  return NULL;
1610  }
1611 
1612  ptr = ptr2;
1613  for (i = 0; i < total; i++)
1614  {
1615  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
1616  if (stx_build_regu_variable (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset], &regu_var_list[i].value) == NULL)
1617  {
1618  return NULL;
1619  }
1620 
1621  if (i < total - 1)
1622  {
1623  regu_var_list[i].next = (struct regu_variable_list_node *) &regu_var_list[i + 1];
1624  }
1625  else
1626  {
1627  regu_var_list[i].next = NULL;
1628  }
1629  }
1630 
1631  return regu_var_list;
1632 }
1633 
1634 static REGU_VARLIST_LIST
1635 stx_restore_regu_varlist_list (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr)
1636 {
1637  REGU_VARLIST_LIST regu_var_list_list;
1638  int offset;
1639  int total;
1640  int i;
1641  char *ptr2;
1642  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
1643 
1644  regu_var_list_list = (REGU_VARLIST_LIST) stx_get_struct_visited_ptr (thread_p, ptr);
1645  if (regu_var_list_list != NULL)
1646  {
1647  return regu_var_list_list;
1648  }
1649 
1650  ptr2 = or_unpack_int (ptr, &total);
1651  regu_var_list_list = (REGU_VARLIST_LIST) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (struct regu_varlist_list_node) * total);
1652  if (regu_var_list_list == NULL)
1653  {
1654  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
1655  return NULL;
1656  }
1657  if (stx_mark_struct_visited (thread_p, ptr, regu_var_list_list) == ER_FAILED)
1658  {
1659  return NULL;
1660  }
1661 
1662  ptr = ptr2;
1663  for (i = 0; i < total; i++)
1664  {
1665  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
1666  regu_var_list_list[i].list = stx_restore_regu_variable_list (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
1667  if (i < total - 1)
1668  {
1669  regu_var_list_list[i].next = (REGU_VARLIST_LIST) (&regu_var_list_list[i + 1]);
1670  }
1671  else
1672  {
1673  regu_var_list_list[i].next = NULL;
1674  }
1675  }
1676 
1677  return regu_var_list_list;
1678 }
1679 
1680 static KEY_RANGE *
1681 stx_restore_key_range_array (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, int nelements)
1682 {
1683  KEY_RANGE *key_range_array;
1684  int *ints;
1685  int i, j, offset;
1686  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
1687 
1688  key_range_array = (KEY_RANGE *) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (KEY_RANGE) * nelements);
1689  if (key_range_array == NULL)
1690  {
1691  goto error;
1692  }
1693 
1694  ints = stx_restore_int_array (thread_p, ptr, 3 * nelements);
1695  if (ints == NULL)
1696  {
1697  return NULL;
1698  }
1699 
1700  for (i = 0, j = 0; i < nelements; i++, j++)
1701  {
1702  key_range_array[i].range = (RANGE) ints[j];
1703 
1704  offset = ints[++j];
1705  if (offset)
1706  {
1707  key_range_array[i].key1 = stx_restore_regu_variable (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
1708  if (key_range_array[i].key1 == NULL)
1709  {
1710  goto error;
1711  }
1712  }
1713  else
1714  {
1715  key_range_array[i].key1 = NULL;
1716  }
1717 
1718  offset = ints[++j];
1719  if (offset)
1720  {
1721  key_range_array[i].key2 = stx_restore_regu_variable (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
1722  if (key_range_array[i].key2 == NULL)
1723  {
1724  goto error;
1725  }
1726  }
1727  else
1728  {
1729  key_range_array[i].key2 = NULL;
1730  }
1731  }
1732 
1733  return key_range_array;
1734 
1735 error:
1736  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
1737  return NULL;
1738 }

1740 /*
1741  * Restore access spec type list as an array to avoid recursion in the server.
1742  * The array size is restored first, then the array.
1743  */
1744 static ACCESS_SPEC_TYPE *
1745 stx_restore_access_spec_type (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char **ptr, void *arg)
1746 {
1747  ACCESS_SPEC_TYPE *access_spec_type = NULL;
1748  int total, i;
1749 
1750  *ptr = or_unpack_int (*ptr, &total);
1751  if (total > 0)
1752  {
1753  access_spec_type = (ACCESS_SPEC_TYPE *) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (ACCESS_SPEC_TYPE) * total);
1754  if (access_spec_type == NULL)
1755  {
1756  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
1757  return NULL;
1758  }
1759  }
1760 
1761  for (i = 0; i < total; i++)
1762  {
1763  *ptr = stx_build_access_spec_type (thread_p, *ptr, &access_spec_type[i], arg);
1764  if (*ptr == NULL)
1765  {
1766  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
1767  return NULL;
1768  }
1769  if (i < total - 1)
1770  {
1771  access_spec_type[i].next = (ACCESS_SPEC_TYPE *) (&access_spec_type[i + 1]);
1772  }
1773  else
1774  {
1775  access_spec_type[i].next = NULL;
1776  }
1777  }
1778 
1779  return access_spec_type;
1780 }

1782 /*
1783  * stx_build_xasl_header () - Unpack XASL node header from buffer.
1784  *
1785  * return : buffer pointer after the unpacked XASL node header
1786  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
1787  * ptr (in) : buffer pointer where XASL node header is packed
1788  * xasl_header (out) : Unpacked XASL node header
1789  */
1790 static char *
1791 stx_build_xasl_header (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, XASL_NODE_HEADER * xasl_header)
1792 {
1793  if (ptr == NULL)
1794  {
1795  return NULL;
1796  }
1797  ASSERT_ALIGN (ptr, INT_ALIGNMENT);
1798 
1799  OR_UNPACK_XASL_NODE_HEADER (ptr, xasl_header);
1800  return ptr;
1801 }

1803 static char *

1805 {

1818

1828  }

2327  break;
2328

2331  break;

2334  break;

2338

2353  }
2354 
2355  if (ptr == NULL)
2356  {
2357  return NULL;
2358  }

2371  }
2372  else

2401

2404  return NULL;
2405 }
2406 
2407 static char *
2408 stx_build_filter_pred_node (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, PRED_EXPR_WITH_CONTEXT * pred)
2409 {
2410  int offset;
2411  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
2412 
2413  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
2414  if (offset == 0)
2415  {
2416  pred->pred = NULL;
2417  }
2418  else
2419  {
2420  pred->pred = stx_restore_pred_expr (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
2421  if (pred->pred == NULL)
2422  {
2423  goto error;
2424  }
2425  }
2426 
2427  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &pred->num_attrs_pred);
2428  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
2429  if (offset == 0 || pred->num_attrs_pred == 0)
2430  {
2431  pred->attrids_pred = NULL;
2432  }
2433  else
2434  {
2435  pred->attrids_pred =
2436  stx_restore_int_array (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset], pred->num_attrs_pred);
2437  if (pred->attrids_pred == NULL)
2438  {
2439  goto error;
2440  }
2441  }
2442 
2443  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
2444  if (offset == 0)
2445  {
2446  pred->cache_pred = NULL;
2447  }
2448  else
2449  {
2450  pred->cache_pred = stx_restore_cache_attrinfo (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
2451  if (pred->cache_pred == NULL)
2452  {
2453  goto error;
2454  }
2455  }
2456 
2457  return ptr;
2458 error:

2555 static char *

2598 static char *
2599 stx_build_method_sig (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, METHOD_SIG * method_sig, int count)
2600 {
2601  int offset;
2602  int num_args, n;
2603  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
2604 
2605  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
2606  assert (offset > 0);
2607  method_sig->method_name = stx_restore_string (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
2608  if (method_sig->method_name == NULL)
2609  {
2610  goto error;
2611  }
2612 
2613  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
2614  assert (offset > 0);
2615  /* is can be null */
2616  method_sig->class_name = stx_restore_string (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
2617 
2618  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, (int *) &method_sig->method_type);
2619  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &method_sig->num_method_args);
2620 
2621  num_args = method_sig->num_method_args + 1;
2622 
2623  method_sig->method_arg_pos = (int *) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (int) * num_args);
2624  if (method_sig->method_arg_pos == NULL)
2625  {
2626  goto error;
2627  }
2628 
2629  for (n = 0; n < num_args; n++)
2630  {
2631  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &(method_sig->method_arg_pos[n]));
2632  }
2633 
2634  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
2635  if (offset == 0)
2636  {
2637  method_sig->next = NULL;
2638  }
2639  else
2640  {
2641  method_sig->next = stx_restore_method_sig (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset], count - 1);
2642  if (method_sig->next == NULL)
2643  {
2644  goto error;
2645  }
2646  }
2647 
2648  return ptr;
2649 
2650 error:
2651  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
2652  return NULL;
2653 }

3356 {
3357  int offset = 0;

3359  char *p;

3387  }
3388  else
3389  {
3390  upd_cls->class_hfid =

3395  }

3397 
3398  /* num_attrs & att_id */
3399  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &upd_cls->num_attrs);

3402  {

3404  }

3406  {

3409  upd_cls->num_attrs * upd_cls->num_subclasses);

3413  }

3417  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &upd_cls->needs_pruning);
3418  /* has_uniques */
3419  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &upd_cls->has_uniques);
3420 
3421  /* num_lob_attrs */
3422  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
3423  if (offset == 0 || upd_cls->num_subclasses == 0)

3441  }

3451  for (i = 0; i < upd_cls->num_subclasses; i++)
3452  {

3463  {
3464  return NULL;
3465  }
3466  }
3467  }
3468  }

3478  }

3675 static char *
3676 stx_build_update_proc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, UPDATE_PROC_NODE * update_info)
3677 {
3678  int offset;
3679  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
3680 
3681  /* classes */
3682  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &update_info->num_classes);
3683  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
3684  if (offset == 0 || update_info->num_classes == 0)
3685  {
3686  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_GENERIC_ERROR);
3687  return NULL;
3688  }
3689  else
3690  {
3691  update_info->classes =
3692  stx_restore_update_class_info_array (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset],
3693  update_info->num_classes);
3694  if (update_info->classes == NULL)
3695  {
3696  goto error;
3697  }
3698  }
3699 
3700  /* assigns */
3701  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &update_info->num_assigns);
3702  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
3703  if (offset == 0 || update_info->num_classes == 0)
3704  {
3705  update_info->assigns = NULL;
3706  }
3707  else
3708  {
3709  update_info->assigns =
3710  stx_restore_update_assignment_array (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset],
3711  update_info->num_assigns);
3712  if (update_info->assigns == NULL)
3713  {
3714  goto error;
3715  }
3716  }
3717 
3718  /* cons_pred */
3719  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
3720  if (offset == 0)
3721  {
3722  update_info->cons_pred = NULL;
3723  }
3724  else
3725  {
3726  update_info->cons_pred = stx_restore_pred_expr (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
3727  if (update_info->cons_pred == NULL)
3728  {
3729  goto error;
3730  }
3731  }
3732 
3733  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &update_info->wait_msecs);
3734  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &update_info->no_logging);
3735  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &update_info->num_orderby_keys);
3736 
3737  /* restore MVCC condition reevaluation data */
3738  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &update_info->num_assign_reev_classes);
3739  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &update_info->num_reev_classes);
3740  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
3741  if (offset == 0 || update_info->num_reev_classes == 0)
3742  {
3743  update_info->mvcc_reev_classes = NULL;
3744  }
3745  else
3746  {
3747  update_info->mvcc_reev_classes =
3748  stx_restore_int_array (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset], update_info->num_reev_classes);
3749  if (update_info->mvcc_reev_classes == NULL)
3750  {
3751  goto error;
3752  }
3753  }
3754 
3755  return ptr;
3756 
3757 error:
3758  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
3759  return NULL;
3760 }

3813 static char *
3814 stx_build_insert_proc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, INSERT_PROC_NODE * insert_info)
3815 {
3816  int offset;
3817  int i;
3818  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
3819 
3820  ptr = or_unpack_oid (ptr, &insert_info->class_oid);
3821 
3822  ptr = or_unpack_hfid (ptr, &insert_info->class_hfid);
3823 
3824  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &insert_info->num_vals);
3825 
3826  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &insert_info->num_default_expr);
3827 
3828  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
3829  if (offset == 0 || insert_info->num_vals == 0)
3830  {
3831  insert_info->att_id = NULL;
3832  }
3833  else
3834  {
3835  insert_info->att_id =
3836  stx_restore_int_array (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset], insert_info->num_vals);
3837  if (insert_info->att_id == NULL)
3838  {
3839  goto error;
3840  }
3841  }
3842 
3843  /* Make space for the subquery values. */
3844  insert_info->vals = (DB_VALUE **) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (DB_VALUE *) * insert_info->num_vals);
3845  if (insert_info->num_vals)
3846  {
3847  if (insert_info->vals == NULL)
3848  {
3849  goto error;
3850  }
3851  for (i = 0; i < insert_info->num_vals; ++i)
3852  {
3853  insert_info->vals[i] = (DB_VALUE *) 0;
3854  }
3855  }
3856 
3857  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
3858  if (offset == 0)
3859  {
3860  insert_info->cons_pred = NULL;
3861  }
3862  else
3863  {
3864  insert_info->cons_pred = stx_restore_pred_expr (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
3865  if (insert_info->cons_pred == NULL)
3866  {
3867  goto error;
3868  }
3869  }
3870 
3871  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &insert_info->has_uniques);
3872  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &insert_info->wait_msecs);
3873  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &insert_info->no_logging);
3874  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &insert_info->do_replace);
3875  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &insert_info->pruning_type);
3876 
3877  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
3878  if (offset == 0)
3879  {
3880  insert_info->odku = NULL;
3881  }
3882  else
3883  {
3884  insert_info->odku = stx_restore_odku_info (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
3885  if (insert_info->odku == NULL)
3886  {
3887  return NULL;
3888  }
3889  }
3890 
3891  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &insert_info->num_val_lists);
3892  if (insert_info->num_val_lists == 0)
3893  {
3894  insert_info->valptr_lists = NULL;
3895  }
3896  else
3897  {
3898  assert (insert_info->num_val_lists > 0);
3899 
3900  insert_info->valptr_lists =
3901  (OUTPTR_LIST **) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (OUTPTR_LIST *) * insert_info->num_val_lists);
3902  if (insert_info->valptr_lists == NULL)
3903  {
3904  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
3905  return NULL;
3906  }
3907  for (i = 0; i < insert_info->num_val_lists; i++)
3908  {
3909  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
3910  if (ptr == 0)
3911  {
3912  assert (0);
3913  return NULL;
3914  }
3915  else
3916  {
3917  insert_info->valptr_lists[i] = stx_restore_outptr_list (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
3918  if (insert_info->valptr_lists[i] == NULL)
3919  {
3920  return NULL;
3921  }
3922  }
3923  }
3924  }
3925 
3926  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
3927  if (offset == 0)
3928  {
3929  insert_info->obj_oid = NULL;
3930  }
3931  else
3932  {
3933  insert_info->obj_oid = stx_restore_db_value (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
3934  if (insert_info->obj_oid == NULL)
3935  {
3936  return NULL;
3937  }
3938  assert (insert_info->obj_oid->need_clear == false);
3939  }
3940 
3941  return ptr;
3942 
3943 error:
3944  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
3945  return NULL;
3946 }

4093 static char *
4094 stx_build_pred_expr (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, PRED_EXPR * pred_expr)
4095 {
4096  int tmp, offset;
4097  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
4098 
4099  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
4100  pred_expr->type = (TYPE_PRED_EXPR) tmp;
4101 
4102  switch (pred_expr->type)
4103  {
4104  case T_PRED:
4105  ptr = stx_build_pred (thread_p, ptr, &pred_expr->pe.pred);
4106  break;
4107 
4108  case T_EVAL_TERM:
4109  ptr = stx_build_eval_term (thread_p, ptr, &pred_expr->pe.eval_term);
4110  break;
4111 
4112  case T_NOT_TERM:
4113  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4114  if (offset == 0)
4115  {
4116  pred_expr->pe.not_term = NULL;
4117  }
4118  else
4119  {
4120  pred_expr->pe.not_term = stx_restore_pred_expr (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4121  if (pred_expr->pe.not_term == NULL)
4122  {
4123  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
4124  return NULL;
4125  }
4126  }
4127  break;
4128 
4129  default:
4130  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE);
4131  return NULL;
4132  }
4133 
4134  return ptr;
4135 }
4136 
4137 static char *
4138 stx_build_pred (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, PRED * pred)
4139 {
4140  int tmp, offset;
4141  int rhs_type;
4142  PRED_EXPR *rhs;
4143  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
4144 
4145  /* lhs */
4146  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4147  if (offset == 0)
4148  {
4149  pred->lhs = NULL;
4150  }
4151  else
4152  {
4153  pred->lhs = stx_restore_pred_expr (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4154  if (pred->lhs == NULL)
4155  {
4156  goto error;
4157  }
4158  }
4159 
4160  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
4161  pred->bool_op = (BOOL_OP) tmp;
4162 
4163  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &rhs_type); /* rhs-type */
4164 
4165  /* Traverse right-linear chains of AND/OR terms */
4166  while (rhs_type == T_PRED)
4167  {
4168  pred->rhs = (PRED_EXPR *) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (PRED_EXPR));
4169  if (pred->rhs == NULL)
4170  {
4171  goto error;
4172  }
4173 
4174  rhs = pred->rhs;
4175 
4176  rhs->type = T_PRED;
4177 
4178  pred = &rhs->pe.pred;
4179 
4180  /* lhs */
4181  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4182  if (offset == 0)
4183  {
4184  pred->lhs = NULL;
4185  }
4186  else
4187  {
4188  pred->lhs = stx_restore_pred_expr (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4189  if (pred->lhs == NULL)
4190  {
4191  goto error;
4192  }
4193  }
4194 
4195  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
4196  pred->bool_op = (BOOL_OP) tmp; /* bool_op */
4197 
4198  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &rhs_type); /* rhs-type */
4199  }
4200 
4201  /* rhs */
4202  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4203  if (offset == 0)
4204  {
4205  pred->rhs = NULL;
4206  }
4207  else
4208  {
4209  pred->rhs = stx_restore_pred_expr (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4210  if (pred->rhs == NULL)
4211  {
4212  goto error;
4213  }
4214  }
4215 
4216  return ptr;
4217 
4218 error:
4219  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
4220  return NULL;
4221 }
4222 
4223 static char *
4224 stx_build_eval_term (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, EVAL_TERM * eval_term)
4225 {
4226  int tmp;
4227 
4228  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
4229  eval_term->et_type = (TYPE_EVAL_TERM) tmp;
4230 
4231  switch (eval_term->et_type)
4232  {
4233  case T_COMP_EVAL_TERM:
4234  ptr = stx_build_comp_eval_term (thread_p, ptr, &eval_term->et.et_comp);
4235  break;
4236 
4237  case T_ALSM_EVAL_TERM:
4238  ptr = stx_build_alsm_eval_term (thread_p, ptr, &eval_term->et.et_alsm);
4239  break;
4240 
4241  case T_LIKE_EVAL_TERM:
4242  ptr = stx_build_like_eval_term (thread_p, ptr, &eval_term->et.et_like);
4243  break;
4244 
4245  case T_RLIKE_EVAL_TERM:
4246  ptr = stx_build_rlike_eval_term (thread_p, ptr, &eval_term->et.et_rlike);
4247  break;
4248 
4249  default:
4250  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE);
4251  return NULL;
4252  }
4253 
4254  return ptr;
4255 }
4256 
4257 static char *
4258 stx_build_comp_eval_term (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, COMP_EVAL_TERM * comp_eval_term)
4259 {
4260  int tmp, offset;
4261  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
4262 
4263  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4264  if (offset == 0)
4265  {
4266  comp_eval_term->lhs = NULL;
4267  }
4268  else
4269  {
4270  comp_eval_term->lhs = stx_restore_regu_variable (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4271  if (comp_eval_term->lhs == NULL)
4272  {
4273  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
4274  return NULL;
4275  }
4276  }
4277 
4278  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4279  if (offset == 0)
4280  {
4281  comp_eval_term->rhs = NULL;
4282  }
4283  else
4284  {
4285  comp_eval_term->rhs = stx_restore_regu_variable (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4286  if (comp_eval_term->rhs == NULL)
4287  {
4288  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
4289  return NULL;
4290  }
4291  }
4292 
4293  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
4294  comp_eval_term->rel_op = (REL_OP) tmp;

4464 
4465 static char *
4466 stx_build_access_spec_type (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, ACCESS_SPEC_TYPE * access_spec, void *arg)
4467 {
4468  int tmp, offset;
4469  int val;
4470  OUTPTR_LIST *outptr_list = NULL;
4471 
4472  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
4473 
4474  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
4475  access_spec->type = (TARGET_TYPE) tmp;
4476 
4477  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
4478  access_spec->access = (ACCESS_METHOD) tmp;
4479 
4480  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4481  if (offset == 0)
4482  {
4483  access_spec->indexptr = NULL;
4484  }
4485  else
4486  {
4487  access_spec->indexptr = stx_restore_indx_info (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4488  if (access_spec->indexptr == NULL)
4489  {
4490  goto error;
4491  }
4492  /* backup index id */
4493  access_spec->btid = access_spec->indexptr->btid;
4494  }
4495 
4496  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4497  if (offset == 0)
4498  {
4499  access_spec->where_key = NULL;
4500  }
4501  else
4502  {
4503  access_spec->where_key = stx_restore_pred_expr (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4504  if (access_spec->where_key == NULL)
4505  {
4506  goto error;
4507  }
4508  }
4509 
4510  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4511  if (offset == 0)
4512  {
4513  access_spec->where_pred = NULL;
4514  }
4515  else
4516  {
4517  access_spec->where_pred = stx_restore_pred_expr (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4518  if (access_spec->where_pred == NULL)
4519  {
4520  goto error;
4521  }
4522  }
4523 
4524  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4525  if (offset == 0)
4526  {
4527  access_spec->where_range = NULL;
4528  }
4529  else
4530  {
4531  access_spec->where_range = stx_restore_pred_expr (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4532  if (access_spec->where_range == NULL)
4533  {
4534  goto error;
4535  }
4536  }
4537 
4538  switch (access_spec->type)
4539  {
4540  case TARGET_CLASS:
4541  case TARGET_CLASS_ATTR:
4542  ptr = stx_build_cls_spec_type (thread_p, ptr, &ACCESS_SPEC_CLS_SPEC (access_spec));
4543  break;
4544 
4545  case TARGET_LIST:
4546  ptr = stx_build_list_spec_type (thread_p, ptr, &ACCESS_SPEC_LIST_SPEC (access_spec));
4547  break;
4548 
4549  case TARGET_SHOWSTMT:
4550  ptr = stx_build_showstmt_spec_type (thread_p, ptr, &ACCESS_SPEC_SHOWSTMT_SPEC (access_spec));
4551  break;
4552 
4553  case TARGET_REGUVAL_LIST:
4554  /* only for the customized type, arg is valid for the transition of customized outptr info */
4555  outptr_list = (OUTPTR_LIST *) arg;
4556  ptr = stx_build_rlist_spec_type (thread_p, ptr, &ACCESS_SPEC_RLIST_SPEC (access_spec), outptr_list);
4557  break;
4558 
4559  case TARGET_SET:
4560  ptr = stx_build_set_spec_type (thread_p, ptr, &ACCESS_SPEC_SET_SPEC (access_spec));
4561  break;
4562 
4563  case TARGET_METHOD:
4564  ptr = stx_build_method_spec_type (thread_p, ptr, &ACCESS_SPEC_METHOD_SPEC (access_spec));
4565  break;
4566 
4567  default:
4568  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE);
4569  return NULL;
4570  }
4571 
4572  if (ptr == NULL)
4573  {
4574  return NULL;
4575  }
4576 
4577  /* access_spec_type->s_id not sent to server */
4578  memset (&access_spec->s_id, '\0', sizeof (SCAN_ID));
4579  access_spec->s_id.status = S_CLOSED;
4580 
4581  access_spec->grouped_scan = false;
4582  access_spec->fixed_scan = false;
4583 
4584  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
4585  access_spec->single_fetch = (QPROC_SINGLE_FETCH) tmp;
4586 
4587  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &access_spec->pruning_type);
4588  access_spec->parts = NULL;
4589  access_spec->curent = NULL;
4590  access_spec->pruned = false;
4591 
4592  access_spec->clear_value_at_clone_decache = false;
4593  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4594  if (offset == 0)
4595  {
4596  access_spec->s_dbval = NULL;
4597  }
4598  else
4599  {
4600  access_spec->s_dbval = stx_restore_db_value (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4601  if (access_spec->s_dbval == NULL)
4602  {
4603  goto error;
4604  }
4605  if (xasl_unpack_info->use_xasl_clone && !db_value_is_null (access_spec->s_dbval))
4606  {
4607  access_spec->clear_value_at_clone_decache = true;
4608  }
4609  }
4610 
4611  access_spec->parts = NULL;
4612  access_spec->curent = NULL;
4613  access_spec->pruned = false;
4614 
4615  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &val);
4616  access_spec->flags = (ACCESS_SPEC_FLAG) val;
4617 
4618  return ptr;
4619 
4620 error:
4621  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
4622  return NULL;
4623 }

4678  }
4679  }
4680 
4681  indx_info->iss_range.key2 = NULL;
4682  }

4917  if (cls_spec->attrids_rest == NULL)
4918  {
4919  goto error;
4920  }
4921  }
4922 
4923  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4924  if (offset == 0)
4925  {
4926  cls_spec->cache_rest = NULL;
4927  }
4928  else
4929  {
4930  cls_spec->cache_rest = stx_restore_cache_attrinfo (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4931  if (cls_spec->cache_rest == NULL)
4932  {
4933  goto error;
4934  }
4935  }
4936 
4937  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
4938  cls_spec->schema_type = (ACCESS_SCHEMA_TYPE) tmp;
4939 
4940  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &cls_spec->num_attrs_reserved);
4941 
4942  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4943  if (offset == 0)
4944  {
4945  cls_spec->cache_reserved = NULL;
4946  }
4947  else
4948  {
4949  cls_spec->cache_reserved =
4950  stx_restore_db_value_array_extra (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset],
4951  cls_spec->num_attrs_reserved, cls_spec->num_attrs_reserved);
4952  if (cls_spec->cache_reserved == NULL)
4953  {
4954  goto error;
4955  }
4956  }
4957 
4958  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4959  if (offset == 0)
4960  {
4961  cls_spec->cls_regu_list_reserved = NULL;
4962  }
4963  else
4964  {
4965  cls_spec->cls_regu_list_reserved =
4966  stx_restore_regu_variable_list (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4967  if (cls_spec->cls_regu_list_reserved == NULL)
4968  {
4969  goto error;
4970  }
4971  }
4972 
4973  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &cls_spec->num_attrs_range);
4974  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
4975  if (offset == 0 || cls_spec->num_attrs_range == 0)
4976  {
4977  cls_spec->attrids_range = NULL;
4978  }
4979  else
4980  {

4983  if (cls_spec->attrids_range == NULL)
4984  {
4985  goto error;
4986  }
4987  }
4988

4990  if (offset == 0)
4991  {
4992  cls_spec->cache_range = NULL;
4993  }
4994  else
4995  {
4996  cls_spec->cache_range = stx_restore_cache_attrinfo (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
4997  if (cls_spec->cache_range == NULL)
4998  {
4999  goto error;
5000  }
5001  }
5002 
5003  return ptr;
5004 
5005 error:

5206 static char *
5207 stx_build_val_list (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, VAL_LIST * val_list)
5208 {
5209  int offset, i;
5210  QPROC_DB_VALUE_LIST value_list = NULL;
5211  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
5212 
5213  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &val_list->val_cnt);
5214 
5215  value_list =
5216  (QPROC_DB_VALUE_LIST) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (struct qproc_db_value_list) * val_list->val_cnt);
5217  if (val_list->val_cnt)
5218  {
5219  if (value_list == NULL)
5220  {
5221  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
5222  return NULL;
5223  }
5224  }
5225 
5226  for (i = 0; i < val_list->val_cnt; i++)
5227  {
5228  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5229  if (offset == 0)
5230  {
5231  value_list[i].val = NULL;
5232  }
5233  else
5234  {
5235  value_list[i].val = stx_restore_db_value (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
5236  if (value_list[i].val == NULL)
5237  {
5238  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
5239  return NULL;
5240  }
5241  assert (value_list[i].val->need_clear == false);
5242  }
5243 
5244  if (i < val_list->val_cnt - 1)
5245  {
5246  value_list[i].next = (QPROC_DB_VALUE_LIST) (&value_list[i + 1]);
5247  }
5248  else
5249  {
5250  value_list[i].next = NULL;
5251  }
5252  }
5253 
5254  val_list->valp = value_list;
5255 
5256  return ptr;
5257 }

5300 static char *
5301 stx_build_regu_variable (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, REGU_VARIABLE * regu_var)
5302 {
5303  int tmp, offset;
5304 
5305  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
5306 
5307  ptr = or_unpack_domain (ptr, &regu_var->domain, NULL);
5308  /* save the original domain */
5309  regu_var->original_domain = regu_var->domain;
5310 
5311  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
5312  regu_var->type = (REGU_DATATYPE) tmp;
5313 
5314  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &regu_var->flags);
5315  assert (!REGU_VARIABLE_IS_FLAGED (regu_var, REGU_VARIABLE_FETCH_ALL_CONST));
5316  assert (!REGU_VARIABLE_IS_FLAGED (regu_var, REGU_VARIABLE_FETCH_NOT_CONST));
5317 
5318  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5319  if (offset == 0)
5320  {
5321  regu_var->vfetch_to = NULL;
5322  }
5323  else
5324  {
5325  regu_var->vfetch_to = stx_restore_db_value (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
5326  if (regu_var->vfetch_to == NULL)
5327  {
5328  goto error;
5329  }
5330  }
5331 
5332  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5333  if (offset == 0)
5334  {
5335  regu_var->xasl = NULL;
5336  }
5337  else
5338  {
5339  regu_var->xasl = stx_restore_xasl_node (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
5340  if (regu_var->xasl == NULL)
5341  {
5342  goto error;
5343  }
5344  }
5345 
5346  ptr = stx_unpack_regu_variable_value (thread_p, ptr, regu_var);
5347 
5348  return ptr;
5349 
5350 error:
5351  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
5352  return NULL;
5353 }
5354 
5355 static char *
5356 stx_unpack_regu_variable_value (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, REGU_VARIABLE * regu_var)
5357 {
5358  REGU_VALUE_LIST *regu_list;
5359  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regu_var_list = NULL;
5360  int offset;
5361  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info_p = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
5362 
5363  assert (ptr != NULL && regu_var != NULL);
5364 
5365  switch (regu_var->type)
5366  {
5367  case TYPE_REGU_VAR_LIST:
5368  ptr = stx_build_regu_variable_list (thread_p, ptr, &regu_var_list);
5369  if (ptr == NULL)
5370  {
5371  goto error;
5372  }
5373  regu_var->value.regu_var_list = regu_var_list;
5374  break;
5375 
5376  case TYPE_REGUVAL_LIST:
5377  regu_list = stx_regu_value_list_alloc_and_init (thread_p);
5378 
5379  if (regu_list == NULL)
5380  {
5381  goto error;
5382  }
5383 
5384  ptr = stx_build_regu_value_list (thread_p, ptr, regu_list, regu_var->domain);
5385  if (ptr == NULL)
5386  {
5387  goto error;
5388  }
5389 
5390  regu_var->value.reguval_list = regu_list;
5391  break;
5392 
5393  case TYPE_DBVAL:
5394  ptr = stx_build_db_value (thread_p, ptr, &regu_var->value.dbval);
5395  if (xasl_unpack_info_p->use_xasl_clone && !db_value_is_null (&regu_var->value.dbval))
5396  {
5397  REGU_VARIABLE_SET_FLAG (regu_var, REGU_VARIABLE_CLEAR_AT_CLONE_DECACHE);
5398  }
5399  break;
5400 
5401  case TYPE_CONSTANT:
5402  case TYPE_ORDERBY_NUM:
5403  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5404  if (offset == 0)
5405  {
5406  regu_var->value.dbvalptr = NULL;
5407  }
5408  else
5409  {
5410  regu_var->value.dbvalptr = stx_restore_db_value (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info_p->packed_xasl[offset]);
5411  if (regu_var->value.dbvalptr == NULL)
5412  {
5413  goto error;
5414  }
5415  if (xasl_unpack_info_p->use_xasl_clone && regu_var->value.dbvalptr->need_clear)
5416  {
5417  REGU_VARIABLE_SET_FLAG (regu_var, REGU_VARIABLE_CLEAR_AT_CLONE_DECACHE);
5418  }
5419  }
5420  break;
5421 
5422  case TYPE_INARITH:
5423  case TYPE_OUTARITH:
5424  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5425  if (offset == 0)
5426  {
5427  regu_var->value.arithptr = NULL;
5428  }
5429  else
5430  {
5431  regu_var->value.arithptr = stx_restore_arith_type (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info_p->packed_xasl[offset]);
5432  if (regu_var->value.arithptr == NULL)
5433  {
5434  goto error;
5435  }
5436  }
5437  break;
5438 
5439  case TYPE_FUNC:
5440  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5441  if (offset == 0)
5442  {
5443  regu_var->value.funcp = NULL;
5444  }
5445  else
5446  {
5447  regu_var->value.funcp = stx_restore_function_type (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info_p->packed_xasl[offset]);
5448  if (regu_var->value.funcp == NULL)
5449  {
5450  goto error;
5451  }
5452  }
5453  break;
5454 
5455  case TYPE_ATTR_ID:
5456  case TYPE_SHARED_ATTR_ID:
5457  case TYPE_CLASS_ATTR_ID:
5458  ptr = stx_build_attr_descr (thread_p, ptr, &regu_var->value.attr_descr);
5459  break;
5460 
5461  case TYPE_LIST_ID:
5462  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5463  if (offset == 0)
5464  {
5465  regu_var->value.srlist_id = NULL;
5466  }
5467  else
5468  {
5469  regu_var->value.srlist_id = stx_restore_srlist_id (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info_p->packed_xasl[offset]);
5470  if (regu_var->value.srlist_id == NULL)
5471  {
5472  goto error;
5473  }
5474  }
5475  break;
5476 
5477  case TYPE_POSITION:
5478  ptr = stx_build_pos_descr (ptr, &regu_var->value.pos_descr);
5479  break;
5480 
5481  case TYPE_POS_VALUE:
5482  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &regu_var->value.val_pos);
5483  break;
5484 
5485  case TYPE_OID:
5486  case TYPE_CLASSOID:
5487  break;
5488 
5489  default:
5490  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE);
5491  return NULL;
5492  }
5493 
5494  return ptr;
5495 
5496 error:
5497  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
5498  return NULL;
5499 }
5500 
5501 static char *
5502 stx_build_attr_descr (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, ATTR_DESCR * attr_descr)
5503 {
5504  int tmp, offset;
5505  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
5506 
5507  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
5508  attr_descr->id = (CL_ATTR_ID) tmp;
5509 
5510  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
5511  attr_descr->type = (DB_TYPE) tmp;
5512 
5513  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5514  if (offset == 0)
5515  {
5516  attr_descr->cache_attrinfo = NULL;
5517  }
5518  else
5519  {
5520  attr_descr->cache_attrinfo = stx_restore_cache_attrinfo (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
5521  if (attr_descr->cache_attrinfo == NULL)
5522  {
5523  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
5524  return NULL;
5525  }
5526  }
5527 
5528  attr_descr->cache_dbvalp = NULL;
5529 
5530  return ptr;
5531 }

5533 static char *
5534 stx_build_pos_descr (char *ptr, QFILE_TUPLE_VALUE_POSITION * position_descr)
5535 {
5536  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &position_descr->pos_no);
5537  ptr = or_unpack_domain (ptr, &position_descr->dom, NULL);
5538  position_descr->original_domain = position_descr->dom;
5539 
5540  return ptr;
5541 }

5551 static char *
5552 stx_build_arith_type (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, ARITH_TYPE * arith_type)
5553 {
5554  int tmp, offset;
5555  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
5556 
5557  ptr = or_unpack_domain (ptr, &arith_type->domain, NULL);
5558  /* save the original domain */
5559  arith_type->original_domain = arith_type->domain;
5560 
5561  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5562  if (offset == 0)
5563  {
5564  arith_type->value = NULL;
5565  }
5566  else
5567  {
5568  arith_type->value = stx_restore_db_value (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
5569  if (arith_type->value == NULL)
5570  {
5571  goto error;
5572  }
5573  assert (arith_type->value->need_clear == false);
5574  }
5575 
5576  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
5577  arith_type->opcode = (OPERATOR_TYPE) tmp;
5578 
5579  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5580  if (offset == 0)
5581  {
5582  arith_type->next = NULL;
5583  }
5584  else
5585  {
5586  arith_type->next = stx_restore_arith_type (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
5587  if (arith_type->next == NULL)
5588  {
5589  goto error;
5590  }
5591  }
5592 
5593  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5594  if (offset == 0)
5595  {
5596  arith_type->leftptr = NULL;
5597  }
5598  else
5599  {
5600  arith_type->leftptr = stx_restore_regu_variable (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
5601  if (arith_type->leftptr == NULL)
5602  {
5603  goto error;
5604  }
5605  }
5606 
5607  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5608  if (offset == 0)
5609  {
5610  arith_type->rightptr = NULL;
5611  }
5612  else
5613  {
5614  arith_type->rightptr = stx_restore_regu_variable (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
5615  if (arith_type->rightptr == NULL)
5616  {
5617  goto error;
5618  }
5619  }
5620 
5621  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5622  if (offset == 0)
5623  {
5624  arith_type->thirdptr = NULL;
5625  }
5626  else
5627  {
5628  arith_type->thirdptr = stx_restore_regu_variable (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
5629  if (arith_type->thirdptr == NULL)
5630  {
5631  goto error;
5632  }
5633  }
5634 
5635  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
5636  arith_type->misc_operand = (MISC_OPERAND) tmp;
5637 
5638  if (arith_type->opcode == T_CASE || arith_type->opcode == T_DECODE || arith_type->opcode == T_PREDICATE
5639  || arith_type->opcode == T_IF)
5640  {
5641  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5642  if (offset == 0)
5643  {
5644  arith_type->pred = NULL;
5645  }
5646  else
5647  {
5648  arith_type->pred = stx_restore_pred_expr (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
5649  if (arith_type->pred == NULL)
5650  {
5651  goto error;
5652  }
5653  }
5654  }
5655  else
5656  {
5657  arith_type->pred = NULL;
5658  }
5659 
5660  /* This member is only used on server internally. */
5661  arith_type->rand_seed = NULL;
5662 
5663  return ptr;
5664 
5665 error:
5666  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
5667  return NULL;
5668 }

5670 static char *
5671 stx_build_aggregate_type (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, AGGREGATE_TYPE * aggregate)
5672 {
5673  int offset;
5674  int tmp;
5675  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info_p = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
5676 
5677  assert (ptr != NULL && aggregate != NULL);
5678 
5679  /* domain */
5680  ptr = or_unpack_domain (ptr, &aggregate->domain, NULL);
5681  aggregate->original_domain = aggregate->domain;
5682 
5683  /* accumulator */
5684  aggregate->accumulator.clear_value_at_clone_decache = false;
5685  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5686  if (offset == 0)
5687  {
5688  aggregate->accumulator.value = NULL;
5689  }
5690  else
5691  {
5692  aggregate->accumulator.value = stx_restore_db_value (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info_p->packed_xasl[offset]);
5693  if (aggregate->accumulator.value == NULL)
5694  {
5695  goto error;
5696  }
5697  if (xasl_unpack_info_p->use_xasl_clone && !db_value_is_null (aggregate->accumulator.value))
5698  {
5699  aggregate->accumulator.clear_value_at_clone_decache = true;
5700  }
5701  }
5702 
5703  aggregate->accumulator.clear_value2_at_clone_decache = false;
5704  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5705  if (offset == 0)
5706  {
5707  aggregate->accumulator.value2 = NULL;
5708  }
5709  else
5710  {
5711  aggregate->accumulator.value2 = stx_restore_db_value (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info_p->packed_xasl[offset]);
5712  if (aggregate->accumulator.value2 == NULL)
5713  {
5714  goto error;
5715  }
5716  if (xasl_unpack_info_p->use_xasl_clone && !db_value_is_null (aggregate->accumulator.value2))
5717  {
5718  aggregate->accumulator.clear_value2_at_clone_decache = true;
5719  }
5720  }
5721 
5722  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &aggregate->accumulator.curr_cnt);
5723 
5724  /* next */
5725  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5726  if (offset == 0)
5727  {
5728  aggregate->next = NULL;
5729  }
5730  else
5731  {
5732  aggregate->next = stx_restore_aggregate_type (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info_p->packed_xasl[offset]);
5733  if (aggregate->next == NULL)
5734  {
5735  goto error;
5736  }
5737  }
5738 
5739  /* function */
5740  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
5741  aggregate->function = (FUNC_TYPE) tmp;
5742 
5743  /* option */
5744  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
5745  aggregate->option = (QUERY_OPTIONS) tmp;
5746 
5747  /* opr_dbtype */
5748  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
5749  aggregate->opr_dbtype = (DB_TYPE) tmp;
5750  aggregate->original_opr_dbtype = aggregate->opr_dbtype;
5751 
5752  /* operand */
5753  ptr = stx_build_regu_variable (thread_p, ptr, &aggregate->operand);
5754  if (ptr == NULL)
5755  {
5756  return NULL;
5757  }
5758 
5759  /* list_id */
5760  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5761  if (offset == 0)
5762  {
5763  aggregate->list_id = NULL;
5764  }
5765  else
5766  {
5767  aggregate->list_id = stx_restore_list_id (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info_p->packed_xasl[offset]);
5768  if (aggregate->list_id == NULL)
5769  {
5770  goto error;
5771  }
5772  }
5773 
5774  /* flag_agg_optimize */
5775  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, (int *) &aggregate->flag_agg_optimize);
5776 
5777  /* btid */
5778  ptr = or_unpack_btid (ptr, &aggregate->btid);
5779 
5780  /* sort_list */
5781  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5782  if (offset == 0)
5783  {
5784  aggregate->sort_list = NULL;
5785  }
5786  else
5787  {
5788  aggregate->sort_list = stx_restore_sort_list (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info_p->packed_xasl[offset]);
5789  if (aggregate->sort_list == NULL)
5790  {
5791  goto error;
5792  }
5793  }
5794 
5795  /* info */
5796  if (aggregate->function == PT_PERCENTILE_CONT || aggregate->function == PT_PERCENTILE_DISC)
5797  {
5798  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
5799  if (offset > 0)
5800  {
5801  aggregate->info.percentile.percentile_reguvar =
5802  stx_restore_regu_variable (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info_p->packed_xasl[offset]);
5803  if (aggregate->info.percentile.percentile_reguvar == NULL)
5804  {
5805  goto error;
5806  }
5807  }
5808  else
5809  {
5810  goto error;
5811  }
5812  }
5813  else if (aggregate->function == PT_CUME_DIST || aggregate->function == PT_PERCENT_RANK)
5814  {
5815  /* init info.dist_percent */
5816  aggregate->info.dist_percent.const_array = NULL;
5817  aggregate->info.dist_percent.list_len = 0;
5818  aggregate->info.dist_percent.nlargers = 0;
5819  }
5820  else
5821  {
5822  /* Other functions need specific variables if any in the future */
5823  ;
5824  }
5825 
5826  /* accumulator_domain */
5827  aggregate->accumulator_domain.value_dom = NULL;
5828  aggregate->accumulator_domain.value2_dom = NULL;
5829 
5830  return ptr;
5831 
5832 error:
5833  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
5834  return NULL;
5835 }

5875  }

5877  return ptr;

6176 static char *
6177 stx_build_connectby_proc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, CONNECTBY_PROC_NODE * stx_connectby_proc)
6178 {

6420 /* stx_build_regu_value_list () -
6421  * return:
6422  * thread_p(in)
6423  * tmp(in) :
6424  * ptr(in) : pointer to REGU_VALUE_LIST
6425  */
6426 static char *
6427 stx_build_regu_value_list (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, REGU_VALUE_LIST * regu_value_list, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
6428 {
6429  int i, count, tmp;
6430  REGU_VALUE_ITEM *list_node;
6431  REGU_VARIABLE *regu;
6432 
6433  assert (ptr != NULL && regu_value_list != NULL);
6434 
6435  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &count);
6436  if (count <= 0)
6437  {
6438  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE);
6439  goto error;
6440  }
6441 
6442  for (i = 0; i < count; ++i)
6443  {
6444  list_node = stx_regu_value_item_alloc_and_init (thread_p);
6445  if (list_node == NULL)
6446  {
6447  goto error;
6448  }
6449 
6450  regu = (REGU_VARIABLE *) stx_get_struct_visited_ptr (thread_p, ptr);
6451  if (regu == NULL)
6452  {
6453  regu = (REGU_VARIABLE *) stx_alloc_struct (thread_p, sizeof (REGU_VARIABLE));
6454  if (regu == NULL)
6455  {
6456  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
6457  goto error;
6458  }
6459 
6460  if (stx_mark_struct_visited (thread_p, ptr, regu) == ER_FAILED)
6461  {
6462  goto error;
6463  }
6464  }
6465 
6466  /* Now, we got a REGU_VARIABLE successfully */
6467  stx_init_regu_variable (regu);
6468  list_node->value = regu;
6469 
6470  if (regu_value_list->current_value == NULL)
6471  {
6472  regu_value_list->regu_list = list_node;
6473  }
6474  else
6475  {
6476  regu_value_list->current_value->next = list_node;
6477  }
6478 
6479  regu_value_list->current_value = list_node;
6480 
6481  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &tmp);
6482  regu->type = (REGU_DATATYPE) tmp;
6483  regu->domain = domain;
6484  /* save te original domain */
6485  regu->original_domain = domain;
6486 
6487  if (regu->type != TYPE_DBVAL && regu->type != TYPE_INARITH && regu->type != TYPE_POS_VALUE)
6488  {
6489  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE);
6490  goto error;
6491  }
6492  ptr = stx_unpack_regu_variable_value (thread_p, ptr, regu);
6493  if (ptr == NULL)
6494  {
6495  goto error;
6496  }
6497 
6498  regu_value_list->count += 1;
6499  }
6500  regu_value_list->current_value = regu_value_list->regu_list;
6501 
6502  return ptr;
6503 
6504 error:
6505  return NULL;
6506 }
6507 
6508 /* stx_build_regu_variable_list () -
6509  * return:
6510  * thread_p(in)
6511  * ptr(out):
6512  * regu_var_list(in): pointer to REGU_VARIABLE_LIST
6513  */
6514 static char *
6515 stx_build_regu_variable_list (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *ptr, REGU_VARIABLE_LIST * regu_var_list)
6516 {
6517  int offset;
6518  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
6519 
6520  assert (ptr != NULL && regu_var_list != NULL);
6521 
6522  ptr = or_unpack_int (ptr, &offset);
6523  if (offset == 0)
6524  {
6525  *regu_var_list = NULL;
6526  }
6527  else
6528  {
6529  *regu_var_list = stx_restore_regu_variable_list (thread_p, &xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl[offset]);
6530  if (*regu_var_list == NULL)
6531  {
6532  return NULL;
6533  }
6534  }
6535 
6536  return ptr;
6537 }

6539 /*
6540  * init_regu_variable () -
6541  * return:
6542  * regu(in): :
6543  */
6544 static void
6545 stx_init_regu_variable (REGU_VARIABLE * regu)
6546 {
6547  assert (regu);
6548 
6549  regu->type = TYPE_POS_VALUE;
6550  regu->flags = 0;
6551  regu->value.val_pos = 0;
6552  regu->vfetch_to = NULL;
6553  regu->domain = NULL;
6554  REGU_VARIABLE_XASL (regu) = NULL;
6555 }
6556 
6557 /*
6558  * stx_mark_struct_visited () -
6559  * return: if successful, return NO_ERROR, otherwise
6560  * ER_FAILED and error code is set to xasl_errcode
6561  * ptr(in) : pointer constant to be marked visited
6562  * str(in) : where the struct pointed by 'ptr' is stored
6563  *
6564  * Note: mark the given pointer constant as visited to avoid
6565  * duplicated storage of a struct which is pointed by more than one node
6566  */
6567 static int
6568 stx_mark_struct_visited (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const void *ptr, void *str)
6569 {
6570  int new_lwm;
6571  int block_no;
6572  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
6573 
6574  if (thread_p == NULL)
6575  {
6576  thread_p = thread_get_thread_entry_info ();
6577  }
6578 
6579  block_no = PTR_BLOCK (ptr);
6580  new_lwm = xasl_unpack_info->ptr_lwm[block_no];
6581 
6582  if (xasl_unpack_info->ptr_max[block_no] == 0)
6583  {
6584  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_max[block_no] = START_PTR_PER_BLOCK;
6585  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[block_no] =
6586  (VISITED_PTR *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, sizeof (VISITED_PTR) * xasl_unpack_info->ptr_max[block_no]);
6587  }
6588  else if (xasl_unpack_info->ptr_max[block_no] <= new_lwm)
6589  {
6590  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_max[block_no] *= 2;
6591  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[block_no] =
6592  (VISITED_PTR *) db_private_realloc (thread_p, xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[block_no],
6593  sizeof (VISITED_PTR) * xasl_unpack_info->ptr_max[block_no]);
6594  }
6595 
6596  if (xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[block_no] == (VISITED_PTR *) NULL)
6597  {
6598  stx_set_xasl_errcode (thread_p, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY);
6599  return ER_FAILED;
6600  }
6601 
6602  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[block_no][new_lwm].ptr = ptr;
6603  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[block_no][new_lwm].str = str;
6604 
6605  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_lwm[block_no]++;
6606 
6607  return NO_ERROR;
6608 }
6609 
6610 /*
6611  * stx_get_struct_visited_ptr () -
6612  * return: if the ptr is already visited, the offset of
6613  * position where the node pointed by 'ptr' is stored,
6614  * otherwise, ER_FAILED (xasl_errcode is NOT set)
6615  * ptr(in) : pointer constant to be checked if visited or not
6616  *
6617  * Note: check if the node pointed by `ptr` is already stored or
6618  * not to avoid multiple store of the same node
6619  */
6620 static void *
6621 stx_get_struct_visited_ptr (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const void *ptr)
6622 {
6623  int block_no;
6624  int element_no;
6625  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
6626 
6627  block_no = PTR_BLOCK (ptr);
6628 
6629  if (xasl_unpack_info->ptr_lwm[block_no] <= 0)
6630  {
6631  return NULL;
6632  }
6633 
6634  for (element_no = 0; element_no < xasl_unpack_info->ptr_lwm[block_no]; element_no++)
6635  {
6636  if (ptr == xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[block_no][element_no].ptr)
6637  {
6638  return (xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[block_no][element_no].str);
6639  }
6640  }
6641 
6642  return NULL;
6643 }
6644 
6645 /*
6646  * stx_free_visited_ptrs () -
6647  * return:
6648  *
6649  * Note: free memory allocated to manage visited ptr constants
6650  */
6651 static void
6652 stx_free_visited_ptrs (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
6653 {
6654  int i;
6655  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
6656 
6657  for (i = 0; i < MAX_PTR_BLOCKS; i++)
6658  {
6659  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_lwm[i] = 0;
6660  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_max[i] = 0;
6661  if (xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[i])
6662  {
6663  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[i]);
6664  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[i] = (VISITED_PTR *) 0;
6665  }
6666  }
6667 }
6668 
6669 /*
6670  * stx_alloc_struct () -
6671  * return:
6672  * size(in) : # of bytes of the node
6673  *
6674  * Note: allocate storage for structures pointed to from the xasl tree.
6675  */
6676 static char *
6677 stx_alloc_struct (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, int size)
6678 {
6679  char *ptr;
6680  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info = stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p);
6681 
6682  if (!size)
6683  {
6684  return NULL;
6685  }
6686 
6687  size = MAKE_ALIGN (size); /* alignment */
6688  if (size > xasl_unpack_info->alloc_size)
6689  { /* need to alloc */
6690  int p_size;
6691 
6692  p_size = MAX (size, xasl_unpack_info->packed_size);
6693  p_size = MAKE_ALIGN (p_size); /* alignment */
6694  ptr = (char *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, p_size);
6695  if (ptr == NULL)
6696  {
6697  return NULL; /* error */
6698  }
6699  xasl_unpack_info->alloc_size = p_size;
6700  xasl_unpack_info->alloc_buf = ptr;
6701  if (xasl_unpack_info->track_allocated_bufers)
6702  {
6703  UNPACK_EXTRA_BUF *add_buff = NULL;
6704  add_buff = (UNPACK_EXTRA_BUF *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, sizeof (UNPACK_EXTRA_BUF));
6705  if (add_buff == NULL)
6706  {
6707  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, ptr);
6708  return NULL;
6709  }
6710  add_buff->buff = ptr;
6711  add_buff->next = NULL;
6712 
6713  if (xasl_unpack_info->additional_buffers == NULL)
6714  {
6715  xasl_unpack_info->additional_buffers = add_buff;
6716  }
6717  else
6718  {
6719  add_buff->next = xasl_unpack_info->additional_buffers;
6720  xasl_unpack_info->additional_buffers = add_buff;
6721  }
6722  }
6723  }
6724 
6725  /* consume alloced buffer */
6726  ptr = xasl_unpack_info->alloc_buf;
6727  xasl_unpack_info->alloc_size -= size;
6728  xasl_unpack_info->alloc_buf += size;
6729 
6730  return ptr;
6731 }
6732 
6733 /*
6734  * stx_init_xasl_unpack_info () -
6735  * return:
6736  * xasl_stream(in) : pointer to xasl stream
6737  * xasl_stream_size(in) :
6738  *
6739  * Note: initialize the xasl pack information.
6740  */
6741 static int
6742 stx_init_xasl_unpack_info (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, char *xasl_stream, int xasl_stream_size)
6743 {
6744  int n;
6745 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
6746  XASL_UNPACK_INFO *xasl_unpack_info;
6747 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
6748  int head_offset, body_offset;
6749 
6750 #define UNPACK_SCALE 3 /* TODO: assume */
6751 
6752  head_offset = sizeof (XASL_UNPACK_INFO);
6753  head_offset = MAKE_ALIGN (head_offset);
6754  body_offset = xasl_stream_size * UNPACK_SCALE;
6755  body_offset = MAKE_ALIGN (body_offset);
6756 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
6757  xasl_unpack_info = (XASL_UNPACK_INFO *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, head_offset + body_offset);
6758  stx_set_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (thread_p, xasl_unpack_info);
6759 #else /* SERVER_MODE */
6760  xasl_unpack_info = (XASL_UNPACK_INFO *) db_private_alloc (NULL, head_offset + body_offset);
6761 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
6762  if (xasl_unpack_info == NULL)
6763  {
6764  return ER_FAILED;
6765  }
6766  xasl_unpack_info->packed_xasl = xasl_stream;
6767  xasl_unpack_info->packed_size = xasl_stream_size;
6768  for (n = 0; n < MAX_PTR_BLOCKS; ++n)
6769  {
6770  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_blocks[n] = (VISITED_PTR *) 0;
6771  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_lwm[n] = 0;
6772  xasl_unpack_info->ptr_max[n] = 0;
6773  }
6774  xasl_unpack_info->alloc_size = xasl_stream_size * UNPACK_SCALE;
6775  xasl_unpack_info->alloc_buf = (char *) xasl_unpack_info + head_offset;
6776  xasl_unpack_info->additional_buffers = NULL;
6777  xasl_unpack_info->track_allocated_bufers = 0;
6778 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
6779  xasl_unpack_info->thrd = thread_p;
6780 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
6781 
6782  return NO_ERROR;
6783 }
6784 
6785 /*
6786  * stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr () -
6787  * return:
6788  */
6789 static XASL_UNPACK_INFO *
6790 stx_get_xasl_unpack_info_ptr (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
6791 {
6792 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
6793  return (XASL_UNPACK_INFO *) thread_p->xasl_unpack_info_ptr;
6794 #else /* SERVER_MODE */
6795  return (XASL_UNPACK_INFO *) xasl_unpack_info;
6796 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
6797 }
6798 
6799 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)
6800 /*
6801  * stx_set_xasl_unpack_info_ptr () -
